  "prompt": "What is the procedure for 48 days Lord Murugan fasting?",
  "response": "The 48-day fasting for Lord Murugan, also known as Kanda Shasti Viratham, is a significant spiritual practice observed by devotees of Lord Murugan. Here is the procedure typically followed during the fasting:\n\n1. **Preparation and Intention**:\n   - Begin with a clear intention to undertake the fasting and seek blessings from Lord Murugan.\n   - Choose a clean and quiet place for daily prayers and meditation.\n\n2. **Dietary Restrictions**:\n   - Avoid consuming meat, fish, eggs, and alcohol.\n   - Follow a vegetarian diet, ideally sattvic food (pure and simple food that is believed to enhance spiritual practices).\n   - Some devotees may also avoid garlic and onions.\n\n3. **Daily Routine**:\n   - Wake up early in the morning, preferably before sunrise.\n   - Take a bath and wear clean clothes.\n   - Visit the temple or a designated prayer area at home.\n\n4. **Prayers and Offerings**:\n   - Perform a puja (ritual worship) to Lord Murugan, which can include lighting a lamp, offering flowers, fruits, and incense.\n   - Recite prayers and hymns dedicated to Lord Murugan such as the Skanda Shasti Kavacham, Kanda Shasti Kavasam, and other Murugan mantras.\n   - Chant the \"Om Saravanabhava\" mantra.\n\n5. **Meditation and Devotion**:\n   - Spend time in meditation, focusing on Lord Murugan\u2019s divine form and attributes.\n   - Engage in reading spiritual texts related to Lord Murugan and his legends.\n\n6. **Observing Austerities**:\n   - Practice self-control and avoid indulgence in sensory pleasures.\n   - Maintain a positive and peaceful mindset, avoiding negative thoughts and actions.\n   - Engage in charity and help others whenever possible.\n\n7. **Weekly Fasting Days**:\n   - Some devotees may choose to observe full fasting (complete abstinence from food) on specific days such as Tuesdays and Fridays, which are considered auspicious for Lord Murugan.\n\n8. **Concluding the Fast**:\n   - On the 48th day, perform a special puja and offer additional prayers and offerings to Lord Murugan.\n   - Seek blessings from elders and spiritual guides.\n   - Break the fast with a simple and sattvic meal.\n\n9. **Celebration**:\n   - Participate in temple activities and community celebrations, if available.\n   - Continue to uphold the spiritual practices and principles learned during the fasting period.\n\nIt is important to approach the fasting with sincerity, devotion, and a pure heart. Devotees may adapt the fasting procedure based on personal capabilities and guidance from spiritual mentors.",
